past.title: First Annual Crawfish Boil
past.description: Join us for Aggies For Limbs' First Annual Crawfish Boil! 100% of the proceeds go to Ashton's Angels to help someone in need of a prosthetic. Enjoy fresh crawfish with all the fixings, live music, and great company for a wonderful cause.

past.title: First Annual Prancing for Prosthetics
past.description: The inaugural Prancing for Prosthetics event that started our annual holiday tradition of combining fitness, festive spirit, and fundraising. This first-ever 5K run/walk demonstrated the strong community support that would become a hallmark of AFL events.

gallery.alt: Large group photo of participants at the First Annual Prancing for Prosthetics event, wearing winter gear and holiday accessories on a rainy day

historical.significance: First running event organized by Aggies for Limbs
historical.legacy: Established the tradition of our annual holiday-themed 5K fundraiser

past.title: Boot Scootin' BBQ 2019
past.description: Our spring fundraiser featuring BBQ and western-themed entertainment. Despite the rain, we had a full crowd turn out to support our cause, demonstrating the strong community backing for Aggies for Limbs' mission.

outcome.achievement: Successful spring fundraiser with strong attendance despite rain

past.title: Fun Run for Prosthetics 2019
past.description: Our Fall 2019 semester culminated in this successful Fun Run event blessed with beautiful running weather and great company. The event brought together students, families, and community members for a morning of fitness and fundraising.

outcome.achievement: Raised over $10,000 to help provide prosthetics for our next angel

past.title: AFL Virtual Walkathon 2020
past.description: In the Fall of 2020, Aggies for Limbs adapted to the COVID-19 pandemic by organizing a virtual walkathon. Members could walk or run a distance of their choice at a location of their choice, allowing for safe participation while maintaining social distancing. This innovative approach enabled us to continue our mission of fundraising for prosthetics while ensuring everyone's safety.
features: Run or walk at your preferred location

outcome.achievement: Successfully adapted to pandemic conditions while maintaining our fundraising mission

past.title: Santa's Stroll 2023

location.name: Lot 50 on Texas A&M University Campus

past.description: Santa's Stroll is Aggies For Limbs' annual 5k event for this semester. A 5k event is held every November or December near Texas A&M University's campus and is open to all families. This event is a fun Christmas themed 5k run or walk to raise money for Ashton's Angels. 100% of proceeds will be given to Ashton's Angels.
features: Dress up in your favorite Christmas gear
Snacks to fill your belly after you run

schedule.notes: Check in will be in the parking lot. There will be free parking at the venue.

earlyBird.note: Ordering by 11/15 guarantees you an event t-shirt

general.note: T-shirts after 11/15 will be first come first serve

past.description: Prancing For Prosthetics is Aggies For Limbs annual 5K. The fun run is held every December on Texas A&M University's campus and is open to all families. This event is a fun Christmas-themed run to raise money for Ashton's Angels. 100% of proceeds will be given to Ashton's Angels.

past.title: 3rd Annual Prancing for Prosthetics 5K
past.description: Join us for our Christmas-themed 5K race benefiting Ashton's Angels! Each participant receives a dri-fit shirt, goodie bag, and a chance to win prizes as one of the top three runners. Bring your Christmas spirit and wear Santa hats, elf suits, antlers, or bells for this festive race. All proceeds go to our philanthropy Ashton's Angels, helping provide prosthetics to those in need.

schedule.notes: Please allow time for check-in as lines can be long. Parking available at Lot 50 near the ETB (Emerging Technology Building).

options.description: Includes race entry and guaranteed shirt

options.name: General Admission
options.description: Includes race entry, shirt not guaranteed

outcome.achievement: Most successful event to date, raising over $10,000 for prosthetic care
